12:T4c5,Jet A-1 is the internationally standardised kerosene-grade aviation turbine fuel meeting both ASTM D1655 and UK DEF STAN 91-091 specifications. XRT Group sources Jet A-1 from the Singapore and Rotterdam refining complexes — the two largest aviation fuel trading hubs globally — for supply into airline procurement programmes, into-plane operators, and strategic fuel reserves.

**Specification**

Flash point 38°C minimum, freeze point -47°C maximum, density 775–840 kg/m³ at 15°C. Full JIG (Joint Inspection Group) chain-of-custody documentation available. SGS conducts certificate of quality and quantity at load port.

**Logistics**

Singapore loading supports Asia-Pacific airline supply and into-plane fuelling at major regional airports. Rotterdam loading covers European and transatlantic routing. Pipeline and dedicated clean-product tanker delivery.

**Pricing**

Priced against Platts Jet/Kero CIF assessment with current indicative premium +$1.50/MT. Term supply agreements with monthly or fortnightly price fixing available through our Energy desk.

**Compliance**

IATA fuel quality standards, JIG aviation fuel quality control, OFAC and EU sanctions screening, FATF AML counterparty due diligence.8:["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-12 pt-10 sm:pt-16 pb-10 sm:pb-12","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_400px] gap-10 lg:gap-16 items-start","children":[["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-6","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"label-caps px-3 py-1.5 border","style":{"color":"#c8111f","borderColor":"#c8111f"},"children":"ENE-004"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"label-caps text-[#A8A5A0]","children":"Energy Commodities"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-[clamp(2.25rem,6vw,4.5rem)] text-white leading-[1.0] mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-barlow)","fontWeight":900,"letterSpacing":"-0.02em","textTransform":"uppercase"},"children":"Jet Fuel A-1"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-base text-[#A8A5A0] mb-8","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-archivo)","letterSpacing":"0.04em"},"children":"ASTM D1655 / DEF STAN 91-091"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-base sm:text-lg text-[#C4C1BE] leading-relaxed mb-10 max-w-xl","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-archivo)"},"children":"Jet Fuel A-1 to ASTM D1655 and DEF STAN 91-091, sourced from Singapore and Rotterdam refining hubs. Platts Jet/Kero benchmark at +$1.50/MT. Minimum 5,000 MT, CIF. SGS inspection. <4 hour desk response."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 border-t border-xrt-steel/15","children":[["$","div","Min. Volume",{"className":"py-5 sm:py-6 border-b sm:border-b-0 sm:border-r border-xrt-steel/15 sm:px-6 sm:first:pl-0","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"label-caps text-[#A8A5A0] mb-2","children":"Min. Volume"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-black text-white","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-barlow)","letterSpacing":"-0.02em"},"children":"5,000 MT"}]]}],["$","div","Benchmark",{"class